{{for|the Church of England suffragan bishop|Anglican Bishop of Plymouth}} {{Infobox Bishopric |border = catholic |font_color = black |bishopric = [[Plymouth]] |coatofarms = |image = |incumbent = [[Mark O'Toole (bishop)|Mark O'Toole]] |province = [[Province of Southwark|Southwark]] |diocese = [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Plymouth|Plymouth]] |cathedral = [[Plymouth Cathedral]] |date = 1850 |website = }} The '''[[Bishop]] of [[Plymouth]]''' is the [[Ordinary (officer)|Ordinary]] of the [[Roman Catholic]] [[Diocese of Plymouth]] in the [[Province of Southwark]], England.<ref name=dplym>{{Catholic-hierarchy|diocese|dplym|Diocese of Plymouth|20 November 2011}}</ref><ref name=gigadplym>[http://www.gcatholic.org/dioceses/diocese/plym0.htm ''Diocese of Plymouth''] at GCatholic.org.com. Retrieved on 14 June 2011.</ref>
The diocese covers an area of {{convert|12831|km2|0|lk=off|abbr=on}} and consists of the counties of [[Cornwall]], [[Devon]] and [[Dorset]]. The [[Episcopal see|see]] is in the [[Plymouth|City of Plymouth]] where the bishop's [[Cathedra|seat]] is located at the [[Plymouth Cathedral|Cathedral Church of Saint Mary and Saint Boniface]].<ref name=dplym/><ref name=gigadplym/>
The diocese of Plymouth was one of the dioceses erected on 29 September 1850 from the [[Vicar Apostolic of the Western District (England)|Vicariate Apostolic of the Western District]].<ref name=dplym/><ref name=gigadplym/> The bishop is the Right Reverend [[Mark O'Toole (bishop)|Mark O'Toole]], the 9th Bishop of Plymouth, who was appointed on 9 November 2013 by [[Pope Francis]].<ref name=CHearld>{{cite news | title =Pope Francis appoints new English bishop | newspaper =[[Catholic Herald]] | location =UK | date =9 November 2013 | url =http://www.catholicherald.co.uk/news/2013/11/09/pope-francis-appoints-new-english-bishop/ | accessdate =9 November 2013}}</ref>
